The paper discusses the degradation mechanisms and pattern dependency in flash memories, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The proposed modulation coding schemes aim to improve data reliability, which involves coding theory and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques to transform vulnerable data patterns into more robust ones, which falls under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AR) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the control and optimization of flash memory systems, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
